Gauteng has received a total of 102,000 new pupils for the 2022 academic year. Masego Rahlaga reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng has received a total of 102,000 new pupils for the 2022 academic year. This is according to Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi. READ: Back to school | Lesufi apologises for unplaced pupils His department has also said all Grade 1 and 8 pupils whose parents applied online but were not allocated space at schools, should all be placed by Friday. “We received 102,000 new learners this year and we will need to build 100 more [schools] to be able to deal with placements," Lesufi said. READ: Back to school | Motshekga: Infrastructure, placements are still big problems "We will need to build a school every month to accommodate everyone because we are lucky in Gauteng, everyone wants to come here”. Inland schools reopened on Wednesday. * eNCA's Masego Rahlaga reports.